acceptOperatorship(address).details: Can only be called by the proposed operator.

params.fromOperator: The previous operator of the contract.

acceptOwnership().details: Can only be called by the pending owner

chainName().details: Gets the name of the chain this is deployed at

constructor.details: All of the variables passed here are stored as immutable variables.

params.chainName_: The name of the chain that this contract is deployed on.

contractCallValue(string,string,bytes).details: If `tokenAddress` is `0`, then value is in terms of the native token, otherwise it's in terms of the token address.

params.payload: The payload sent with the call.
params.sourceAddress: The source address on the source chain.

returns._1: uint256 The value the call is worth.

returns._0: bytes32 The contract id of this contract.

deployInterchainToken(bytes32,string,str.details: At least the `gasValue` amount of native token must be passed to the function call. `gasValue` exists because this function can be part of a multicall involving multiple functions that could make remote contract calls. If minter is empty bytes, no additional minter is set on the token, only ITS is allowed to mint. If the token is being deployed on the current chain, minter should correspond to an EVM address (as bytes). Otherwise, an encoding appropriate to the destination chain should be used.

params.decimals: The decimals of the token to be deployed.
params.destinationChain: The name of the destination chain to deploy to.
params.gasValue: The amount of native tokens to be used to pay for gas for the remote deployment.
params.minter: The address that will be able to mint and burn the deployed token.
params.name: The name of the token to be deployed.
params.salt: The salt to be used during deployment.
params.symbol: The symbol of the token to be deployed.

returns.tokenId: The tokenId corresponding to the deployed InterchainToken.

deployedTokenManager(bytes32).details: This function checks if a token manager contract exists at the address for the specified tokenId. If no token manager is deployed for the tokenId, the function will revert with `TokenManagerDoesNotExist`.

params.tokenId: The tokenId of the deployed token manager.

returns.tokenManager_: The instance of ITokenManager associated with the specified tokenId.

params.payload: The encoded data payload for the transaction.
params.sourceAddress: The address of the remote ITS where the transaction originates from.
params.sourceChain: The chain where the transaction originates from.

expressExecute(bytes32,string,string,byt.details: This function is `payable` because non-payable functions cannot be called in a multicall that calls other `payable` functions.

params.payload: The encoded data payload for the transaction.
params.sourceAddress: The address of the remote ITS where the transaction originates from.
params.sourceChain: The chain where the transaction originates from.

returns.expressExecutor: The address of the express executor.

returns._0: True if the account has the role, false otherwise

interchainTokenAddress(bytes32).details: The token does not need to exist.

params.tokenId: The tokenId of the interchain token.

returns.tokenAddress: The address of the interchain token.

params.salt: The salt that the deployer uses for the deployment.
params.sender: The address of the TokenManager deployer.

returns.tokenId: The tokenId that the custom TokenManager would get (or has gotten).

interchainTransfer(bytes32,string,bytes,.details: The function retrieves the TokenManager associated with the tokenId.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be transferred.
params.destinationAddress: The address on the destination chain to send the tokens to.
params.destinationChain: The destination chain to send the tokens to.
params.metadata: Optional metadata for the transfer. The first 4 bytes is the metadata version. To call the `destinationAddress` as a contract with a payload, provide `bytes.concat(bytes4(0), payload)` as the metadata. The token will be transferred to the destination app contract before it is executed.
params.tokenId: The unique identifier of the token to be transferred.

returns._0: bool Boolean value representing whether or not the address is an operator.

isTrustedAddress(string,string).details: Checks whether the interchain sender is a trusted address

returns._0: bool true if the sender chain/address are trusted, false otherwise

linkToken(bytes32,string,bytes,uint8,byt.details: This function replaces the prior `deployTokenManager` function.

params.destinationChain: The chain to link the token to. Pass an empty string for this chain.
params.destinationTokenAddress: The token address to link, as bytes.
params.gasValue: Pass a non-zero value only for remote linking, which should be the gas to use to pay for the contract call.
params.linkParams: Additional parameteres to use to link the token. Fow not it is just the address of the operator.
params.salt: A unique identifier to allow for multiple tokens registered per deployer.
params.tokenManagerType: The type of the token manager to use to send and receive tokens.

returns.tokenId: The tokenId associated with the token manager.

params.tokenId: the tokenId of the registered token.

multicall(bytes[]).details: This function requires that the contract has sufficient balance for the delegate calls. If any of the calls fail, the function will revert with the failure message.

params.data: An array of encoded function calls

returns.results: An bytes array with the return data of each function call

returns.owner_: The current owner of the contract

returns.paused_: A boolean representing the pause status. True if paused, false otherwise.

returns.owner_: The pending owner of the contract

proposeOperatorship(address).details: Can only be called by the current operator.

params.operator: The address of the new operator.

proposeOwnership(address).details: Can only be called by the current owner. The ownership does not change until the new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to

params.salt: A unique salt to derive tokenId from.
params.tokenManagerType: The type of the token manager to use for the token registration.

params.gasValue: The cross-chain gas value for sending the registration message to ITS Hub.

registeredTokenAddress(bytes32).details: This function requires that a token manager is already deployed for the specified tokenId. It will call `deployedTokenManager` to get the token manager and return the address of the associated token.

params.tokenId: The tokenId of the registered token.

params.chain: The chain to set the trusted address of.

params.tokenIds: An array of the tokenIds of the tokenManagers to set the flow limits of.

params.paused: Boolean value representing whether to pause or unpause.

params.address_: The address to set as trusted.
params.chain: The chain to set the trusted address of.

setup(bytes).details: This function is only callable by the proxy contract.

tokenManagerAddress(bytes32).details: The TokenManager does not need to exist already.

returns.tokenManagerAddress_: The deployment address of the TokenManager.

returns._0: tokenManagerAddress The address of the TokenManager implementation.

transferOperatorship(address).details: Can only be called by the current operator.

params.operator: The address of the new operator.

transferOwnership(address).details: Can only be called by the current owner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to

transmitInterchainTransfer(bytes32,addre.details: Only callable by a token registered under a tokenId.

params.amount: The amount of token to give.
params.destinationChain: The name of the chain to send tokens to.
params.metadata: Optional metadata for the call for additional effects (such as calling a destination contract).
params.sourceAddress: The address where the token is coming from.
params.tokenId: The tokenId of the token (which must be the msg.sender).

trustedAddress(string).details: Gets the trusted address at a remote chain

params.chain: Chain name of the remote chain

returns.trustedAddress_: The trusted address for the chain. Returns '' if the chain is untrusted

trustedAddressHash(string).details: Gets the trusted address hash for a chain

returns.trustedAddressHash_: the hash of the trusted address for that chain

upgrade(address,bytes32,bytes).details: This function is only callable by the owner.

params.newImplementation: The address of the new implementation contract
params.newImplementationCodeHash: The codehash of the new implementation contract
params.params: Optional setup parameters for the new implementation contract

acceptOperatorship(address).notice: Accept a proposed change of operatorship.

chainNameHash().notice: Returns the hash of the chain name.

constructor.notice: Constructor for the Interchain Token Service.

contractCallValue(string,string,bytes).notice: Returns the amount of token that this call is worth.

deployInterchainToken(bytes32,string,str.notice: Used to deploy an interchain token alongside a TokenManager in another chain.

deployedTokenManager(bytes32).notice: Returns the instance of ITokenManager from a specific tokenId.

expressExecute(bytes32,string,string,byt.notice: Express executes operations based on the payload and selector.

getExpressExecutor(bytes32,string,string.notice: Returns the express executor for a given command.

hasRole(address,uint8).notice: Checks if an account has a role.

implementation().notice: Returns the address of the current implementation

interchainTokenAddress(bytes32).notice: Returns the address of the interchain token associated with the given tokenId.

interchainTokenDeployer().notice: Returns the address of the interchain token deployer contract.

interchainTokenFactory().notice: Returns the address of the interchain token factory.

interchainTokenId(address,bytes32).notice: Calculates the tokenId that would correspond to a link for a given deployer with a specified salt.

interchainTransfer(bytes32,string,bytes,.notice: Initiates an interchain transfer of a specified token to a destination chain.

isOperator(address).notice: Query if an address is a operator.

linkToken(bytes32,string,bytes,uint8,byt.notice: If `destinationChain` is an empty string, this function will register the token address on the current chain. Otherwise, it will link the token address on the destination chain with the token corresponding to the tokenId on the current chain. A token manager is deployed on EVM chains that's responsible for managing the linked token.

migrateInterchainToken(bytes32).notice: Allows the owner to migrate minter of native interchain tokens from ITS to the corresponding token manager.

multicall(bytes[]).notice: Performs multiple delegate calls and returns the results of all calls as an array

owner().notice: Returns the current owner of the contract.

paused().notice: Check if the contract is paused

pendingOwner().notice: Returns the pending owner of the contract.

proposeOperatorship(address).notice: Propose a change of the operator of the contract.

proposeOwnership(address).notice: Propose to transfer ownership of the contract to a new account `newOwner`.

registerCustomToken(bytes32,address,uint.notice: Only to be used by the InterchainTokenFactory to register custom tokens to this chain. Then link token can be used to register those tokens to other chains.

registerTokenMetadata(address,uint256).notice: Registers metadata for a token on the ITS Hub. This metadata is used for scaling linked tokens. The token metadata must be registered before linkToken can be called for the corresponding token.

registeredTokenAddress(bytes32).notice: Returns the address of the token that an existing tokenManager points to.

removeTrustedAddress(string).notice: Used to remove a trusted address for a chain.

setFlowLimits(bytes32[],uint256[]).notice: Used to set a flow limit for a token manager that has the service as its operator.

setPauseStatus(bool).notice: Allows the owner to pause/unpause the token service.

setTrustedAddress(string,string).notice: Used to set a trusted address for a chain.

setup(bytes).notice: Sets up the contract with initial data

tokenHandler().notice: Returns the address of TokenHandler implementation.

tokenManagerAddress(bytes32).notice: Calculates the address of a TokenManager from a specific tokenId.

tokenManagerDeployer().notice: Returns the address of the token manager deployer contract.

tokenManagerImplementation(uint256).notice: Getter function for TokenManager implementation. This will mainly be called by TokenManager proxies to figure out their implementations.

transferOperatorship(address).notice: Change the operator of the contract.

transferOwnership(address).notice: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account `newOwner`.

transmitInterchainTransfer(bytes32,addre.notice: Transmit an interchain transfer for the given tokenId.

upgrade(address,bytes32,bytes).notice: Upgrades the contract to a new implementation
